The Mask Personally Identifiable Information (PII) Setting Has Been Removed

Copilot actions apply Einstein Trust Layer data masking by default, so the Mask personally identifiable information (PII) setting has been removed from custom and standard copilot action inputs and outputs. The Trust Layer uses a combination of pattern matching and machine learning techniques to automatically identify and mask PII, no additional settings required.

Where: This change applies to Lightning Experience, the Salesforce mobile app for iOS and Android, the Field Service mobile app for iOS and Android, and Sales Cloud Everywhere in Enterprise, Performance, and Unlimited editions with the Einstein for Sales, Einstein for Service, or Einstein Platform add-on. Setup for Einstein Copilot is available on the desktop site.

When: This change applies starting the week of June 17, 2024.
title: Removed PII Setting in Salesforce
